    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're creating a program to help a digital crossing guard remind people to look both ways before crossing the street. Every time a pedestrian approaches, the program should deliver the same safety reminder. You'll define the reminder once and reuse it for each crossing.\r\n\r\n1. Define a function called `look_both_ways()` that prints a safety message.\r\n\r\n2. Call the function **four times** to represent four people crossing the street.\r\n\r\n3. Make sure the same message prints each time.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nWhen you need to do the same task over and over, a function helps you keep your code short and easy to read. You can call the function as many times as you need.\r\n\r\nUse the **UMPIRE** strategy to understand what's happening, make a plan, test your output, and explain your thinking.",
